The paper deals with distributed constructions of graph spanners, which are relevant to algorithms, distributed systems, and computer networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves graph theory and algorithms, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper's focus on computer networks and communication suggests categories such as cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper involves geometric algorithms, which suggests the category cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
